      <description>&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;ve created an excel workbook to help with calculations. I will be updating it as needed throughout the semester. It&amp;rsquo;s available in 3 formats:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.mathologist.net/files/statway.xlsx&#34;&gt;Click here to download xlsx (for Microsoft Excel).&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;../static/files/statway.ods&#34;&gt;Click here to download ods (LibreOffice or OpenOffice).&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;https://drive.google.com/open?id=1cQAY7yrZAuipdvJae8he64GtOHEwLB8jl4Ct6r2VmV0&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Click here to access the document on Google Drive.&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;ve also created a program for the TI Calculator that will calculate the expected numbers for the \(\chi^2\) test for independence / homogeneity. You can download it 
&lt;a href=&#34;../static/files/CHISQ.8xp&#34;&gt;here.&lt;/a&gt;
 Or you can code it yourself. The code is as follows:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-text&#34; data-lang=&#34;text&#34;&gt;: dim([A])→L₆
: L₆(1)→R
: L₆(2)→C
: Matr▶list(cumSum([A])ᵀ,R,L₆
: sum(L₆)→T
: {R,C}→dim([B]
: For(I,1,R)
: For(J,1,C)
: Matr▶list([A]ᵀ,I,L₆
: Matr▶list([A],J,L₅
: sum(L₅)*sum(L₆)/T → [B](I,J)
: End
: End
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;m also redoing some of the Statway online tools to make them (IMHO) better. So far I have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;http://stats.mathologist.net/mms/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;M&amp;amp;M Proportion Simulator&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;http://stats.mathologist.net/normal/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Normal Distribution Calculator&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;http://stats.mathologist.net/t/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Student T Distribution Calculator&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
